.\" OUT OF THE USE OF THIS SOFTWARE, EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF
.\" SUCH DAMAGE.
.\"
.Dd $Mdocdate: May 31 2007 $
.Dt GETPAGESIZE 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm getpagesize
.Nd get system page size
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In unistd.h
.Ft int
.Fn getpagesize void
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Bf -symbolic
This interface is obsoleted by
.Xr sysconf 3 .
Use
.Fn sysconf _SC_PAGESIZE .
.Ef
.Pp
The
.Fn getpagesize
function returns the number of bytes in a page.
Page granularity is the granularity of many of the memory
management calls.
.Pp
The page size is a system
page size and may not be the same as the underlying
hardware page size.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr pagesize 1 ,
.Xr sbrk 2 ,
.Xr sysconf 3
.Sh HISTORY
The
.Fn getpagesize
function call appeared in
.Bx 4.2 .
@


